being%20able%20to%20access%20apps%20directly%20from%20developers%20outside%20the%20Play%20Store%2C%20at%20price%20points%20chosen%20by%20the%20developers%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20justices%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20why%20they%20denied%20Google's%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAndroid%20provides%20more%20choice%20for%20users%20and%20developers%20than%20any%20mobile%20OS%2C%20and%20the%20changes%20ordered%20by%20the%20US%20District%20Court%20will%20jeopardize%20users'%20ability%20to%20safely%20download%20apps%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Google%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20we're%20disappointed%20the%20order%20isn't%20stayed%2C%20we%20will%20continue%20our%20appeal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dispute%20stems%20from%20a%202020%20lawsuit%20in%20which%20Epic%20Games%20sued%20Google%2C%20alleging%20that%20the%20company%20was%20running%20an%20illegal%20monopoly%20over%20its%20Android%20app%20download%20restrictions%20and%20in-app%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202023%2C%20a%20California%20jury%20ruled%20in%20favor%20of%20Epic%20Games%2C%20finding%20that%20Google's%20policies%20for%20the%20Play%20Store%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-loses-app-store-antitrust-suit-against-fortnite-creators-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eviolated%20antitrust%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E.%20US%20District%20Judge%20James%20Donato%20then%20ordered%20Google%20to%20open%20Android%20to%20competing%20app%20stores%20and%20allow%20developers%20to%20use%20their%20own%20billing%20systems%20for%20a%20period%20of%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20upheld%20that%20verdict.%20In%20September%2C%20Google%20filed%20a%20stay%2C%20requesting%20that%20the%20ordered%20remedies%20be%20put%20on%20hold%20while%20the%20company%20works%20on%20filing%20a%20full%20appeal%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20by%20October%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court's%20rejection%20of%20Google's%20request%20means%20that%20the%20lower%20court's%20orders%20must%20be%20implemented%20by%20October%2022.%20The%20changes%20will%20remain%20unless%20Google's%20full%20appeal%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20successful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-finds-apple-executive-lied-under-oath-refers-criminal-investigation-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20its%20App%20Store%20also%20faced%20a%20similar%20case%20from%20Epic%20Games%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20similar%20remedies.%20The%20iPhone%20maker%20has%20now%20lost%20its%20latest%20appeal%20to%20pause%20these%20remedies%20in%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit.%20Some%20of%20these%20changes%2C%20such%20as%20allowing%20links%20to%20external%20payments%2C%20have%20already%20been%20implemented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEpic%20Games%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-scotus-antitrust-appeal-play-store-epic-fortnite-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1759802590000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e44a605dbc4fd10daa4aac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-scotus-antitrust-appeal-play-store-epic-fortnite-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20denied%20Google's%20bid%20to%20temporarily%20block%20parts%20of%20a%20lower%20court%20ruling%20in%20its%20legal%20fight%20with%20Epic%20Games%2C%20the%20maker%20of%20Fortnite.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22katherineli%40insider.com%20(Katherine%20Li)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A31%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-scotus-antitrust-appeal-play-store-epic-fortnite-2025-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22